// Regression guard, not part of the fix: EqEq/NotEq already had
// (Value::Float, Value::Float) arms (ops.rs) before this fix — only the four
// ordering comparisons (Lt/Gt/LtEq/GtEq) were missing theirs. Pinning
// existing-correct behavior so a future change to ops.rs can't silently
// regress float equality while touching the ordering operators.
print(3.14 == 3.14)
print(3.14 != 2.0)
